##Block the gate to block the return of the city, such measures really good epidemic prevention

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The following article is from Caijing 11, written by Wang Bo and others

Set up by the Industry Reporting Team of Caijing magazine to study the success and failure of enterprises, explore the rise and fall of industries, and promote sunshine business

In the eyes of the legal profession, all over the country to take their own "village" , "closed area" and other extreme practices suspected of illegal. Prevention and control of the epidemic requires a national chess game, not "sweep under the rug. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The community stepped up registration checks but did not turn away tenants

| CAIJING reporters Wang Bo, Zhou Yuan, Chen Xiaoxiao, Ma Lin, Wang Feng, Yang Liyun, Wu Qiong

Editor | Yu LE

Wang Xiaoshan (not his real name) , who rents a room in Dongsanqi village, a town in the north of Beijing, had planned to take a train home on the ninth day of the Lunar New Year, but now he worries that he won't be able to get in when he returns to Beijing.

Wang is from Linfen, Shanxi Province, where he has worked for more than five years. A year ago, Wang rented a one-bedroom on 84 mu of land in Dongsanqi village for about 1,500 yuan a month. Dongsanqi village is located on 84 mu of land next to the subway line 5 Tiantongyuan North Station. There are many two-story buildings, each of which can accommodate more than 20 residents.

On January 30, the village committee of Beiqi village in Beiqi town, Changping District, Beijing, issued a notice, announcing that tenants from outside Beijing would not be allowed to enter the residential area from that day. Other communities in North Qijia, Longhua County have taken similar steps. The landlord called Wang and told him not to come back until the epidemic was over.

As the Lunar New Year holiday draws to a close, more and more people are preparing to return to cities such as Beijing, Shanghai and Guangzhou from their hometowns, despite government policies at all levels to extend the holiday and delay returning to work. How to avoid epidemics caused by returnees is a real test for these cities, but can simply shutting them out and making them homeless really play a positive role in preventing and controlling the epidemic? Residential Committees, property and other institutions to prohibit residents to go home, and whether there is sufficient legal basis?

"Fengcun" , "Fengqu" , all over the "soil method" frequent

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Closures like the one in northern Qijia, Longhua County affect quite a few people. Ye Liang (not his real name) is the founder and CEO of Wang's company, which employs more than 20 people, including Ye, who is from other places (but not from Hubei) and has gone home for the Lunar New Year. Ye said the company now has four non-local staff may not be able to return to Beijing on time. Because they rented "a village house, " their landlord refused to let them back unless they had a "14-day security certificate in Beijing. ". Other field staff rent is a formal community, there is no "home can not go back" situation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Overview of 84 mu of land in Dongsanqi village, Changping District, Beijing, Source: Baidu Map

Faced with the situation of not being able to return home, Wang was not angry. "It's not the landlord's idea, it's the decision of the village committee, " Wang told Caijing. As for how to calculate the rent for the period, he also said that he has not yet considered.

Another reason for the lack of anger, Wang admits, is that his company is now allowing him to delay his return to Beijing.

Although he was a little anxious, Ye said he could only allow the four employees to delay their return to Beijing. "I think at most one month [ the situation ] will be over, too, " Ye said.

But when reporters asked what would happen if it took more than a month, both Ye Liang and Wang Xiaoshan felt embarrassed.

Yu Yang (not his real name) , the owner of West Lake Sinchon-dong, a town in the north of the country, returned home on Jan. 29 from his hometown in Hunan Province. But some neighbors who returned home the next day were not so lucky.

"On the 5th day, I was allowed to come back to the residential area. On the 6th day, it was closed, not only for the tenants, but also for many of the owners who returned to Beijing from other places, " Yu Yang said. On January 30, the West Lake Sinchon-dong Community Group Property Release Notice: In order to prevent the spread of the disease, the West Lake Sinchon-dong community has been closed, non-local people returning to Beijing can not enter.

On January 31, CAIJING reporter called West Lake Xincun Residential Property and Neighborhood Committee confirmed the news. The property staff said that the property has no right to prohibit residents from returning to Beijing, but both the tenants and the owners can not enter the residential area in Kyoto now, and they need to be quarantined outside for 14 days, after which they also need to go to the hospital for examination and provide relevant health certificates, and the route back to Beijing.

CAIJING reporter found that Beijing Chaoyang District near Datun road several small areas also adopted such a closed approach. An owner said that at present, people entering and leaving several residential areas on Datun road need to carry their identity cards and property certificates. That is to say, only the owners of the residential areas can go in and out normally. The people renting the houses have been forbidden to return, and they need to isolate themselves for 14 days, and present a valid health certificate to enter normally.

Some communities have also adopted a degree of closure, but it is relatively less extreme. Mr Wang, a tenant in Tujingjiayuan, Haidian District, plans to return to work in the near future after returning home for the Spring Festival. Tujingjiayuan in the Internet to see such a residential area to prevent people from returning to Beijing to enter the news, he made a phone call in the morning of January 31 residential properties. Property told him, this morning just received instructions, in addition to Hubei, other areas of Beijing returned personnel can enter the community, but to fill out the registration form and sign the letter of commitment. The pledge includes a 14-day isolation at home, a ban on leaving the house except to buy groceries, and a daily temperature test twice a day. Property also stressed that if they do not comply with the above provisions, the village committee will call the police people out of the area.

The xifuhe Garden Complex in Dengjiayao, Tongzhou, is also off-limits to Hubei residents returning to the capital, but the Dengjiayao village committee has commandeered a Shangkeyou hotel at the entrance to the park and ordered Hubei residents to stay there for two weeks. Dengjiayao village committee relevant responsible person said that the specific how to resettle Beijing personnel above no specific arrangements, is the decision of the village committee meeting. "We don't allow people to go home, we have to find a good place for them to live. During the period of isolation, we are responsible for the food and daily necessities of the residents under isolation. " It is understood that the Dengjiayao village committee has provided about 300,000 yuan in total, 55 rooms rented.

Mr. Huang, a resident of the Zhaofeng Xinyuan community in Fengtai district, said that on January 28, the property in the community issued access cards to all residents. Access cards are required to enter the community from the beginning of the two days. Those who do not have access cards will be told that they will not be in the community on January 28 and will be gently advised to leave the community, let's quarantine ourselves.

Other cities have gated communities. As of January 31,537 people had been diagnosed in Zhejiang, the country's second most affected region, and faced with the upcoming return peak, some neighborhoods issued notices asking landlords and tenants to check themselves before returning home after the Lantern Festival.

In Wenyi community, a Five Confucian virtues street near Alibaba's headquarters, the residents'committee issued an emergency notice on January 29, saying that all migrants returning to Hangzhou would not be allowed to enter the community until 2400 hours on the 16th day of the first lunar month (February 9)  Only upon notification by the higher authorities, such as the specific time for the Hubei nationals to return to Hangzhou, can they rent the Xixi Beiyuan and the Zhoujiadou agricultural residence. All costs of control and segregation arising from failure to comply with this requirement will be borne by the lessor (landlord) .

Ms. Chen, who rents a room at the city's Hutou Chen Huayuan, an E-commerce Company in Hangzhou, returned to work in early February, but she is still stuck at home in Ningbo. Residential Property informed her, received notification of the community, the tenant January 17(February 10) after the door.

"The ultimate aim of community prevention and control is to ensure people's health and safety. "

The practice of "village closures" in places such as northern Qijia, Longhua County has caused controversy online. Many netizens think the measure is too strict, and many others suspect it is against the law. According to regulations, Beijing is February 3 to resume work, so will soon usher in the return peak, some industry insiders worry that if the continuation of this one-size-fits-all approach, the related problems will become more and more serious.

An owner of the Gardens in Chaoyang District City of Daiyu said she felt the strict ban on migrant workers returning to their Beijing homes was an extreme measure, and that she had communicated with her neighborhood committee, at present, there are no restrictions on their own community to return to Beijing, normal registration, do a good job of self-isolation or protection.

One of the tenants living in Beijing's Changying Pixel North district, whose hometown is in Jilin, did not leave Beijing during the Lunar New Year because of work. He shared a flat with two other tenants, one from Zhejiang and the other from Jiangxi, as of 2400 hours on January 30, there were 537 confirmed cases in Zhejiang and 240 in Jiangxi. He said the two neighbors had returned home for the Lunar New Year and had not yet returned to Beijing. He said he prayed that his neighbors would come back when the outbreak had eased off, but he saw no reason to turn them away.

Regarding the question whether the control measures are suspected of violating the law, the staff of Xihu Xincun Community in Beiqi town did not respond positively. "The residents' committee has been trying to dissuade you. For the sake of the safety of the community, please cooperate with us. The nearby community has been quarantined for the situation of people returning from other places. We didn't say we wouldn't let you go back. If it is necessary or necessary, let the unit arrange room and board."

Yu Yang and many returned to Beijing owners are looking for the coordination of the Property Committee, "the daughter and her husband will return to Beijing in a few days, but also worried that they can not enter the community. "

Zhao Hu, a partner of Beijing Zhongwen Law Firm, told CAIJING that there is no legal basis for the practice in some residential areas. In accordance with Article 42 of China's Law on the prevention and control of infectious diseases, residents are prohibited from returning to their homes for intermediate acts, which require the consent and instructions of the Government of the People's Republic of China at or above the county level. The Neighborhood Committee and the street office also have no such power.

According to the law on Prevention and control of infectious diseases, even if there are special circumstances that require isolation of a certain area, during isolation, it is not possible to distinguish between owners and tenants. If the area is uninhabitable and the tenant can not be isolated, this is a violation of the tenant's rights.

According to Zhao Hu, the district prohibits tenants from going home. What is involved is whether the administrative unit has the right to make such a request. If not, the district behavior is illegal.

He suggested that if returning to Beijing tenants encounter a similar situation, they can report the problem to the relevant units, such as the Neighborhood Committee, the street office or even higher levels, and ask for a solution. The tenant shall have the right to request the executing unit to produce relevant documents and notices. If there is evidence as to who made the decision, the tenant can preserve the evidence and sue.

Beijing law firm lawyer Zhou Zhaocheng also told the "CAIJING" reporter, property owners based on authorization and "property services contract" for the management of the community; In some cities, residents'committees and villagers'committees manage their areas on the basis of relevant laws and public interests. However, any management can not take a geographical discrimination approach. This is because it neither respects human rights nor is illegal and is contrary to the right to equality enshrined in our Constitution.

"The community property or neighborhood or village committees do not consider whether the residents who legally live in the community have returned from the epidemic area, nor do they give advance notice, measure their body temperature, and simply refuse to go home. I think infringement, discrimination and violation of the law should be stopped immediately,"Zhou said.

Zhou Zhaocheng said that the property does not allow access to the circumstances of the community, the legal tenants can be in accordance with the law and the community property for communication, negotiation. And for the lessee if the legal lease of the community, can also seek help from the lessor. The lessor is also under an obligation under the lease to ensure the tenant's occupancy and, if not, to provide temporary accommodation for the tenant.

Indeed, apartment rental agencies are already taking action to protect tenants'rights. In response to Caijing, the person-in-charge said that the situation of tenants not being able to return to their homes is currently an individual case, and that they are making efforts to follow up on the case. Some of the cases have been resolved. For example, the ban on Toujing Jiayuan has been lifted, and tenants have returned to their rental housing units one after another today.

According to "CAIJING" understand, at present, the country has more than 100 million tenants, about half of Beijing. It's a loss to the tenants, to the long-term condo operators. At present, individual landlords account for 70-80% of the rental market in Beijing. Compared with long-term tenants, it is more difficult for individual tenants to safeguard their rights.

In addition to legal issues, a one-size-fits-all "village" , "community" approach to the prevention and control of the epidemic can play a positive role is also questionable. In both cases, the aim of prevention and control measures is to reduce the exposure and aggregation of populations, thus blocking the transmission of the virus. However, if residents can not enter the community, home can not go back, they can only wander outside. For themselves and others, this only increases, not decreases, the risk of transmission. Prevention and control of the epidemic requires a national chess game, not "sweep the snow at each door. ".

On January 31, the city of Beijing announced it would postpone working hours until February 10 for all but essential industries. Zhao Jigui, deputy director of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Civil Affairs, said when talking about the prevention and control measures taken by various communities, "Some communities are too strict in their enforcement, and we will try to dissuade them from doing so. There should be no panic or invisible pressure, " he added, the ultimate aim of community prevention and control is to ensure people's health and safety. Mutual support is the mass basis for winning this epidemic prevention war.

"We want to prevent and control the virus, not to prevent and control our compatriots from all over the world. The practice of targeting people returning to the city, such as residential properties, has long been suspected of violating the law and is by no means necessary to control and cut off infection, " said Zhou Zhaocheng, a lawyer.
